Beverley Davis was supposed to be caring for 89-year-old Ray Warren at his home . 
  But she tricked him into handing over his bank cards to steal £9,164 over 42 transactions . 
  The mother-of-three used his cards to buy Chinese takeaways and pay for creche fees . 
  She gained his trust by lending him £6,000 and paying him £30 a week . 
  Mr Warren was so traumatised he stopped going out and died five months later . 
  Davis pleaded guilty to fraud and was jailed for a year at Portsmouth Crown Court . 
 